<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id5a505c60-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c" identifier="/us/usc/t29/s568"><num value="568">§ 568.</num><heading> Acceptance of donations by Secretary</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Labor is authorized to accept, in the name of the Department of Labor, and employ or dispose of in furtherance of authorized activities of the Department of Labor, during the fiscal year ending <date date="1995-09-30">September 30, 1995</date>, and each fiscal year thereafter, any money or property, real, personal, or mixed, tangible or intangible, received by gift, devise, bequest, or otherwise.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id5a505c61-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/333/tI/s105">Pub. L. 103–333, title I, § 105</ref>, <date date="1994-09-30">Sept. 30, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/2548">108 Stat. 2548</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id5a505c62-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id5a505c63-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
